Mexico Stocks: Televisa, TV Azteca Decline; Penoles Advances

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-08-17T20:41:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/mexico-stocks-televisa-tv-azteca-decline-penoles-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.3 percent to 34,049.58.  Broadcasters followed U.S. technology companies lower. Dell
Inc. tumbled in U.S. trading as slower spending on PCs and
consumer technology crimped its sales forecast.  TV Azteca SAB (AZTECACP MM), Mexico’s second-largest
broadcast television network, dropped 2.6 percent to 7.84 pesos.
 Grupo Televisa SA (TLEVICPO)  , the world’s largest Spanish-
language broadcaster, fell 1.4 percent to 48.88 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, advanced 2.2 percent to 510.15 pesos. Silver
futures for September delivery rose as much as 2 percent to
$40.33 an ounce on the Comex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
